<subSubSection lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[667,1193,1409,1759]" lastBlockId="29.[128,654,213,1067]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="28" pageNumber="28">
COMMENTS: Rothschild did not designate a type in the original description or indicate how many specimens he examined, but later, he (
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild, W." box="[716,998,1648,1670]" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 58" refId="ref127013" refString="Rothschild, W. 1893 g. The avifauna of Laysan and the neighbouring islands: with a complete history to date of the birds of the Hawaiian possessions. Parts 1 and 2. London: R. H. Porter, xiv + 126 pp., pls. 1 - 58." type="book chapter" year="1893">
Rothschild, 
<quantity box="[866,939,1648,1669]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.893" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" unit="g" value="1893.0">1893g</quantity>
: 103
</bibRefCitation>
) gave measurements for 
<specimenCount box="[805,910,1678,1700]" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" type="adult">11 adult</specimenCount>
males and two adult females, with comments on a specimen of a ‘‘young male.’’ 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[846,1081,1737,1759]" pageId="28" pageNumber="28" pagination="123 - 178" refId="ref119004" refString="Hartert, E. 1919 a. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. B. Types in the general collection. Novitates Zoologicae 26: 123 - 178." type="journal article" year="1919">Hartert (1919a: 170)</bibRefCitation>
listed the specimen bearing Palmer’s no. 1688 as the type, thereby designating it the 
<typeStatus box="[541,650,242,264]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">lectotype</typeStatus>
. This specimen is also marked ‘‘Type,’’ ‘‘pl. 11’’ (?), ‘‘52’’ (plate no. in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild, W." box="[428,641,302,324]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 58" refId="ref127013" refString="Rothschild, W. 1893 g. The avifauna of Laysan and the neighbouring islands: with a complete history to date of the birds of the Hawaiian possessions. Parts 1 and 2. London: R. H. Porter, xiv + 126 pp., pls. 1 - 58." type="book chapter" year="1893">
Rothschild, 
<quantity box="[569,641,302,324]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.893" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" unit="g" value="1893.0">1893g</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
), and ‘‘p. 123 Ibis 1893’’ (should be page 112). The following 
<specimenCount box="[298,504,361,383]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" type="generic" typeStatus="paralectotypes">10 paralectotypes</specimenCount>
, collected by Palmer on Maui in 1892, are in AMNH; the remainder were probably exchanged by Rothschild before the collection came to AMNH or may be in BMNH as part of the Rothschild Bequest: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[372,553,509,530]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453529</emphasis>
(Palmer no. 1689), male, 4 August; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[469,654,539,560]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453530</emphasis>
(1697), 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[229,423,568,589]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453531</emphasis>
(1696), males, 9 August; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,428,598,619]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453532</emphasis>
(1712), male, 10 August; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,428,628,649]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453533</emphasis>
(1717), male, 11 August; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[237,426,657,678]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453534</emphasis>
(1743), immature male, 16 August; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[365,555,687,708]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453535</emphasis>
(1719), male, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[220,423,717,738]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453536</emphasis>
(1729), 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453537</emphasis>
(1730), females, 13 August; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">AMNH 453538</emphasis>
(–), unsexed, only 1892 on label, all collected by Palmer. AMNH 453536 is also marked ‘‘pl. 11’’ the significance of which I was unable to determine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[128,654,213,1067]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">
According to Palmer’s diary (
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild, W." pageId="29" pageNumber="29" pagination="59 - 83" refId="ref127068" refString="Rothschild, W. 1900. The avifauna of Laysan and the neighbouring islands: with a complete history to date of the birds of the Hawaiian possessions. Part 3. London: R. H. Porter, xx + 127 - 320, (Di) 1 - (Di) 21, pls. 59 - 83." type="journal article" year="1900">Rothschild, 1900</bibRefCitation>
: (Di)), he was camped at 
<quantity box="[514,600,925,947]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" unit="ft" value="5000.0">5000 ft</quantity>
<date pageId="29" pageNumber="29" value="1892-08-01" valueMax="1892-08-06" valueMin="1892-08-01">1–6 August 1892</date>
and then moved up to the crater of Mount Haleakala (
<geoCoordinate box="[428,517,984,1005]" degrees="20.43" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" precision="555" value="20.43">20.43N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[544,650,984,1006]" degrees="156.10" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" precision="555" value="-156.1">156.10W</geoCoordinate>
, Times atlas) for the remainder of August.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[128,654,213,1067]" box="[157,480,1044,1067]" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis box="[157,290,1044,1067]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="29">
H. l. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rothschild" authorityYear="1893" box="[220,290,1044,1065]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Hemignathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
may be extinct.
</paragraph>
